text.section:
In addition to the powers set forth elsewhere in this article, a savings bank may:
Receive deposits of money from:
Any person;
The federal government or its agencies; and
Any state or its political subdivisions;
Pledge collateral to secure the deposits of:
The federal government or its agencies; or
Any state or its political subdivisions;
On good security:
Invest deposits; and
Make loans from deposits;
Subject to § 4-603 of this title:
Borrow money; and
Pledge its assets to secure the debt;
Rent its vaults or safe-deposit boxes and, in accordance with the rental agreement, permit deposits of property;
Subject to § 5-503 of this article, buy, hold, and convey real property;
Subject to § 4-604 of this title, act as trustee under:
The federal Self-Employed Individuals Tax Retirement Act of 1962; or
The federal Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974;
With the prior approval of the Commissioner, exercise the powers granted under § 3-207 of this article to a trust company; and
Exercise all of the powers usual in carrying on a business of savings banking.
